## Queue Configuration

### RabbitMQ Setup
```bash
# Configure RabbitMQ virtual hosts
ansible {{ region }}_queue -m shell -a "
  rabbitmqctl add_vhost {{ environment }}
"

# Create queues
{% for queue in queues | default(['email', 'notification', 'processing', 'audit', 'backup']) %}
ansible {{ region }}_queue -m shell -a "
  rabbitmqctl declare queue {{ queue }}_{{ region }} durable=true
"
{% endfor %}

# Configure queue policies
ansible {{ region }}_queue -m shell -a "
  rabbitmqctl set_policy ha-all '.*' '{\"ha-mode\":\"all\"}'
"
```

### Worker Configuration
```bash
# Update worker configuration
ansible {{ region }}_worker -m template -a "
  src=worker-config.j2
  dest=/opt/worker/config/worker.conf
"

# Restart worker services
ansible {{ region }}_worker -m systemd -a "name=worker state=restarted"
```

